Users in BWreg2


1. Privacy
2. Scope


1. Privacy
==========
A user should be able to define exactly what he or she wants displayed about him or herself.

This is stored in the "private" field of the user table.

NULL means everything is displayed.
The following lists characters in the "private" coloumn and what they hide:

u - Username
f - First name
l - Last name
m - Mail address
b - Birth year
a - Address
p - Phone
x - Extra
g - Groups

BWReg2 admins and genre admins can READ this information regardless. This 
require "r" permission on BWReg2 or a <gname> list. 

2. Scope
========
User scope is beyond all genres. They are in essence the largest scope.

